result.execSummary:
The defendant Dancia K McGeshick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fraud/Innkeeper,etc-Nonpayment (<=$2500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.21(1m)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Solicitation of], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Intentionally Abuse Hazardous Substance [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.316(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:23 AM Defendant Dancia K McGeshick in court with attorney Chad Lynch.  Defendant Dancia K McGeshick in custody.   Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:22 AM. Called 16CM97, 17CM206, 18CM16 and 18CM24. Court - updates parties on where we are at today as this matter was resheduled from last week due to the reluctance of the Court's intention to accept a probation offer.  Lynch makes additional comment in regards to Court's statement - resolved - on 17CM206 - plead to count #1 as alleged (with repeater enhancer), on 18CM16 - plead to count #1 as alleged, and on 18CM24 - plead to count #1 as alleged - joint recommendation on those case of a withheld sentence and place on probation for 2 years probation - consecutive to any current sentence that she is serving, typical probation conditions, other counts on those cases would be DRI,  on 16CM97 - asking for concurrent jail time to what was previously I&S of 24 months. State responds - makes clarification of the concurrent time to what she is currently setting; conditions of probation to include: AODA and follow thru, no entry into any bars, taverns or similar establishments, 160 hours of community service, employment/school, maintain absolute sobriety, costs on each count. Lynch and McGeshick agree. McGeshick pleads NC to count #1 as alleged on all three cases (17CM206, 18CM16 and 18CM24). Court dismisses and reads in count #2 on cases 18CM16 and 18CM24. Court makes sure the defendant knows what it means for a count to be DRI. Court has plea questgionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constititional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Lynch makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - does believe that she is a candidate for Wellness Court - does not believe that prison is appropriate - currently serving a 24 month sentence due to revocation of an I&S sentence - has sat 220 days in custody - asking to 220 days of jail time on 16CM97 on each count (#1, #4 and #5) - concurrent to each other and concurrent to what she is now serving. State makes additional statement prior to Court's sentencing. McGeshick makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: on 17CM206 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years, on 18CM16 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years, on 18CM24 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years - all probation is concurrent to each other,  conditions of probation: AODA and follow thru, enroll and successuly complete an inpatient substance abuse program to be arranged within 30 days of release from custody and must start inpatient within 60 days of release from custody, impose 6 months of conditional jail on each count - consecutive to each other - stayed - Court will be lifted upon any indication of any probation violations and it will be at the Court's discretion as to how much time the defendant will serve with each violation, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, 160 hours community service, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, costs on each count - 60 DTP after release from custody or inpatient; on 16CM97 - all three counts - impose 9 months - concurrent with each other and concurrent to 17CM58 and 17CM52 - credit for 404 days , civil judgement for unpaid costs, submit DNA sample, appeal rights given, eligible for community service under 973.03(3), adjourned. Court makes statement in regards to the FOSO asking for a furlough due to the pregnancy of the defendant, Court has not made a ruling on that, leaves it up to counsel to file something in regards to that and Court will consider it once received (furlough).
Not called on the record as inmate was at a doctor's appointment at time of hearing.

Defendant Dancia K McGeshick in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Defendant Dancia K McGeshick in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:57 PM. State - change of plea and proceed to sentencing. Scholke and McGeshick agrees. State - have complied with victim notification requirements and has filed restitution report - defendant would plead to counts #1, #3, #4 and #5 as alleged, remaining counts to be DRI, joint recommendation on counts #3 - 45 day straight jail sentence; on counts #1, #4 and #5 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years on each count - concurrent to each other but consecutive to jail time on count #3; condition of probation to include: count #1 - restitution of $235.95 - includes VW surcharge - joint and several with co-defendants - Patricia Nunway and Liann Soman; AODA and follow thru, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars, taverns or similar establishments, maintain/obtain full time employment/school - would like her to get HS diploma or equivalent if she does not have one, 150 hours of community service, no contact with Lianne Soman or Patricia Nunway. Scholke and McGeshick agree and McGeshick understands what it means to have a count DRI. Court dismisses and reads in count #2 & #6. McGeshick pleads NC to counts #1, #3, #4 and #5 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Scholke makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - credit for 130 days. McGeshick makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #3 - 45 days in FC jail - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - credit for 130 days and any remainder to be applied to probation if revoked after good time is configured; counts #1, #4 and #5 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years on each count - concurrent to each other but consecutive to jail time on count #3(time served) with conditions of: count #1 - restitution of $235.95 - includes VW surcharge - joint and several with co-defendants - Patricia Nunway and Lianne Soman - paid at rate of $25/month commencing 30 days after release from incarceration from Langlade County/CO; AODA and follow thru, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars, taverns or similar establishments, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, obtain GED, 100 hours of community service - to be completed within the first 1.5 years or probation, no contact with Lianne Soman or Patricia Nunway, costs on each count - paid at rate of $25.00/month commencing 30 days after release from incarceration from Langlade County/CO, submit DNA sample, right to appeal. Scholke asks for expunction. State has no objections. Court finds eligible expunction under 973.015 upon successful discharge from probation and verification that she has completed all conditions of probation, adjourned.
Adjourned initial appearance on March 29, 2017 at 01:00 pm.
